---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="CNC Precision Services | R. West & Son">
  <Nav />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero-gradient min-h-[60vh] flex items-center justify-center relative overflow-hidden hero-dots">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 z-[5] pointer-events-none opacity-60 md:opacity-30" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 70% at center, rgba(253,249,243,0.95) 0%, rgba(253,249,243,0.8) 40%, rgba(253,249,243,0) 100%);"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-32">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-primary-container/10 px-4 py-1 rounded-full mb-8">
        <span class="text-primary font-label text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider">&#9733; CNC Precision</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-headline text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-[5.5rem] tracking-tighter leading-[0.9] mb-8">
        The router that makes <span class="grad-maroon-text serif-italic">everything fit.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10 leading-relaxed">
        We've got a CNC router in the workshop. It cuts foam, timber, and sheet materials to whatever shape we need, accurate to a fraction of a millimetre. Before CNC, "close enough" meant gaps. Gaps mean movement. Movement means damage. The router changed what's possible.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/r-west/contact" class="grad-maroon-bg text-on-primary px-8 py-3.5 rounded-full font-label text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-widest hover:scale-105 transition-transform inline-block text-center">Tell Us What You Need Cut</a>
        <a href="tel:01752664345" class="border-2 border-primary-container/20 text-primary px-8 py-3.5 rounded-full font-label text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-widest hover:bg-surface-container-low transition-colors inline-block text-center">Call Jason</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What It Actually Does -->
  <section class="py-24 px-8 bg-surface-container-low">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-16 anim-up">
        <span class="inline-block grad-maroon-bg text-on-primary px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Capabilities</span>
        <h2 class="font-headline text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tighter leading-none">
          Three things <span class="grad-maroon-text italic">we cut.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-lg leading-relaxed mt-6 max-w-3xl">
          A CNC router is a computer-controlled cutting machine. You feed it a design, it cuts the material. Foam, plywood, softwood, MDF, composite panels. The computer doesn't get tired, doesn't rush the last cut of the day, doesn't round up a measurement because it's close enough.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- CNC image grid -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-12">
        <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden img-zoom">
          <img class="w-full h-auto object-cover aspect-square" alt="CNC machine at R. West & Son" src="/r-west/images/cnc-machine-branded.webp" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden img-zoom">
          <img class="w-full h-auto object-cover aspect-square" alt="CNC-routed foam insert for precision packing" src="/r-west/images/fb-foam-insert-grid.webp" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden img-zoom">
          <img class="w-full h-auto object-cover aspect-square" alt="CNC-routed wooden box components" src="/r-west/images/fb-foam-insert-angle.webp" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 anim-stagger">
        <!-- Foam Inserts -->
        <div class="bg-surface p-8 rounded-2xl border border-outline-variant/30 anim-up">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary-container text-4xl mb-6">view_in_ar</span>
          <h3 class="font-headline text-2xl mb-4">Foam Inserts</h3>
          <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-base leading-relaxed mb-4">
            This is where most of our CNC work happens. We take the dimensions of your item, whether it's a bronze sculpture, a medical device, or a set of precision instruments, and cut a block of closed-cell foam to its exact three-dimensional profile.
          </p>
          <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-base leading-relaxed">
            The item drops in and can't move. Not sideways, not up, not forward. Zero clearance where it matters. You've seen this in camera cases and tool kits. Same principle. But we're cutting inserts for items that weigh 50kg, or 200kg, or that have irregular shapes no off-the-shelf case could hold.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Timber Panels -->
        <div class="bg-surface p-8 rounded-2xl border border-outline-variant/30 anim-up">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary-container text-4xl mb-6">carpenter</span>
          <h3 class="font-headline text-2xl mb-4">Timber Panels &amp; Components</h3>
          <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-base leading-relaxed">
            Precision-cut plywood panels for packing cases. Interlocking components for multi-item cases where internal dividers need to slot together exactly. Base boards drilled to bolt-hole patterns for skid-mounting heavy equipment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Signs and Displays -->
        <div class="bg-surface p-8 rounded-2xl border border-outline-variant/30 anim-up">
          <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-primary-container text-4xl mb-6">signpost</span>
          <h3 class="font-headline text-2xl mb-4">Signs &amp; Displays</h3>
          <p class="text-on-surface-variant text-base leading-relaxed">
            The same router that cuts foam inserts also cuts lettering, logos, and shaped panels from timber and sheet materials. Packaging is the core work, but if you need precision-cut signage or display elements, the capability is there.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Precision Matters -->
  <section class="py-24 px-8">
    <div class="bg-[#4A0D19] rounded-lg p-12 md:p-24 max-w-7xl mx-auto text-on-primary relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="relative z-10 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-start text-left">
        <!-- Left column: heading + text -->
        <div>
          <span class="inline-block bg-surface/20 text-surface px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">The Difference</span>
          <h2 class="font-headline text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tighter leading-tight mb-8">
            Why precision matters <span class="text-primary-fixed-dim italic">inside a crate.</span>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-on-primary/80 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
            The outside of a crate is obvious. Everyone can see the timber, the bolts, the ISPM15 stamp. But the inside is where the real protection happens.
          </p>
          <p class="text-on-primary/80 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
            An item rattling inside a crate is an item getting damaged. Doesn't matter how strong the outer case is. If there's a 5mm gap between the foam and the object, that's 5mm of movement on every bump, every lift, every drop from forklift to container floor.
          </p>
          <p class="text-on-primary/80 text-xl leading-relaxed font-headline italic">
            The CNC router eliminates that gap. The foam matches the item. The item matches the foam. Nothing moves.
          </p>
          <p class="text-on-primary/60 text-base leading-relaxed mt-8">
            When you're shipping something irreplaceable across an ocean, that difference is everything.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Right column: image + comparison cards -->
        <div>
          <div class="rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-8 img-zoom">
            <img class="w-full h-auto object-cover aspect-[4/3]" alt="Jason working on the CNC machine at R. West & Son" src="/r-west/images/jase-cnc-working.webp" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-white/5 p-6 rounded-lg backdrop-blur">
              <p class="font-headline text-lg text-white mb-2">"Carefully packed"</p>
              <p class="text-on-primary/60 text-sm">Hand-cut foam. Close enough. Gaps filled with padding materials.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white/10 p-6 rounded-lg backdrop-blur border border-primary-fixed-dim/30">
              <p class="font-headline text-lg text-primary-fixed-dim mb-2">"Engineered to be stationary"</p>
              <p class="text-on-primary/60 text-sm">CNC-cut foam. Exact profile. Zero movement in transit.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Can Cut -->
  <section class="py-24 px-8 bg-surface-container-low">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-16 anim-up">
        <span class="inline-block grad-maroon-bg text-on-primary px-4 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Materials</span>
        <h2 class="font-headline text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-tighter leading-none">
          What we can <span class="grad-maroon-text italic">cut.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto anim-up">
        <table class="w-full text-left">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b-2 border-primary-container/30">
              <th class="font-headline text-base py-4 pr-8">Material</th>
              <th class="font-headline text-base py-4 pr-8">What We Make From It</th>
              <th class="font-headline text-base py-4">Typical Use</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-on-surface-variant text-base">
            <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
              <td class="py-4 pr-8 font-headline text-on-surface">Closed-cell foam</td>
              <td class="py-4 pr-8">Profile inserts, cavity blocks, cushioning layers</td>
              <td class="py-4">Internal protection for fragile, heavy, and high-value items</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
              <td class="py-4 pr-8 font-headline text-on-surface">Plywood</td>
              <td class="py-4 pr-8">Case panels, dividers, base boards</td>
              <td class="py-4">Packing case construction and internal structuring</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
              <td class="py-4 pr-8 font-headline text-on-surface">Softwood</td>
              <td class="py-4 pr-8">Crate components, battens, framing</td>
              <td class="py-4">Crate and pallet construction</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-outline-variant/20">
              <td class="py-4 pr-8 font-headline text-on-surface">MDF</td>
              <td class="py-4 pr-8">Shaped panels, signage blanks</td>
              <td class="py-4">Signs, displays, and smooth-finish components</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-4 pr-8 font-headline text-on-surface">Composite sheet</td>
              <td class="py-4 pr-8">Panels, cut shapes</td>
              <td class="py-4">Specialist applications</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-xl">
        <div class="bg-surface p-5 rounded-lg border border-outline-variant/30">
          <p class="font-label text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-primary mb-1">Tolerance</p>
          <p class="font-headline text-2xl">+/- 0.5mm</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-surface p-5 rounded-lg border border-outline-variant/30">
          <p class="font-label text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-primary mb-1">Cutting Area</p>
          <p class="font-headline text-2xl">Large format</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-12 px-8">
    <div class="grad-maroon-bg rounded-lg p-12 md:p-20 max-w-7xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-12 relative overflow-hidden anim-scale">
      <div class="relative z-10 max-w-2xl text-center md:text-left">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-5xl md:text-7xl text-white tracking-tighter leading-none mb-6">
          Need something cut <span class="text-primary-fixed-dim italic">to size?</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-white/80 text-xl md:text-2xl font-headline mb-10">A foam insert for a one-off shipment. A batch of precision panels. The router is ready. Tell us what you need and we'll work out the best approach.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5">
          <a href="/r-west/contact" class="bg-white text-[#69001c] px-12 py-5 rounded-full font-label text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-widest hover:scale-105 transition-transform shadow-lg inline-block text-center">Start Your Quote</a>
          <a href="tel:01752664345" class="border-2 border-white/40 text-white px-12 py-5 rounded-full font-label text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-widest hover:bg-white/15 transition-colors inline-block text-center">Call Jason</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="relative z-10 w-full md:w-1/3">
        <img class="w-full drop-shadow-2xl translate-y-8 rounded-lg" alt="CNC-built wooden box by R. West & Son" src="/r-west/images/fb-crate-build.webp" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
